ctice. I was learning to play the piano, and we were always having rows over it. And my eldest brother. And to try and get us to practice mother and father said to us one day, when you can play Bluebells of the Scotland, a duet, I'll give you five shillin
g
s each. Of course five shillings was a lot in those days, but I don't think we ever practiced so much in our lives until we learned to - oh yes, we did. Oh yes. I think - I can only remember 'em grumbling at us when we wouldn't do things like that. That t
hey wanted us, and it was for our own benefit of course.
